/*
  Irregular geodesic sphere - filled triangle panels + RAISED frame
  (Teufelsberg triangular-radome pattern).
  Units: millimeters.  GENERATED by generate_triangulated.py - edit that, not this.

  The surface is 180 filled triangular panels (a closed faceted shell - the space
  bounded by the triangles is filled, so it is opaque, not see-through). On top runs
  a network of RAISED round struts along every one of the 270 edges, with a hub at
  each of the 92 nodes - the frame of the real dome. Vertices are jittered so the
  triangles vary in size/shape (less regular than a uniform grid).

  Renders fast with the Manifold backend (see README). Regenerate with:
      python3 generate_triangulated.py <freq> <jitter> > geosphere.scad
*/

